    "methodology": "Overseas visitor spending is from the ONS International Passenger Survey (IPS), which surveys passengers at UK air, sea, and tunnel ports. Domestic tourism spending combines the Great Britain Tourism Survey (overnight trips) and Great Britain Day Visits Survey. Employment figures include direct tourism roles and estimated indirect/induced employment from the Tourism Satellite Account methodology. All values are nominal (not inflation-adjusted). The COVID-19 pandemic caused unprecedented disruption to data collection in 2020-21; some figures for those years are estimates.",
